You know that, don't you?

209
00:16:41,132 --> 00:16:42,644
l know.

210
00:16:53,531 --> 00:16:54,520
Well, Victor. . .

211
00:16:56,612 --> 00:16:58,125
. . .l'll leave the rest to you.

212
00:16:58,332 --> 00:17:00,971
ls it okay if l dress her
and get her out of here?

213
00:17:01,172 --> 00:17:04,721
No, l'd keep her here
for another hour.

214
00:17:04,932 --> 00:17:06,365
Another hour?

215
00:17:07,971 --> 00:17:11,009
Then l'd have someone take her home.

216
00:17:16,811 --> 00:17:18,244
Good night, Mandy.

217
00:17:21,092 --> 00:17:23,208
l can't thank you enough for this.

218
00:17:23,932 --> 00:17:26,048
-You saved my ass.
-l' m glad l was here.

219
00:17:26,251 --> 00:17:28,606
Bill, l probably. . . .

220
00:17:29,372 --> 00:17:32,807
l know l don't have to mention this. . .

221
00:17:33,051 --> 00:17:35,805
. . .but this is just between us.

222
00:17:36,291 --> 00:17:37,486
Of course.

223
00:17:38,011 --> 00:17:39,205
Thanks.

224
00:17:59,372 --> 00:18:03,762
l think l've had
a little too much champagne.

225
00:18:06,771 --> 00:18:10,208
l think l have to go
and find my husband now.

226
00:18:10,412 --> 00:18:14,848
But l' m sure he'll be all right
on his own a little longer.

227
00:18:17,291 --> 00:18:18,611
Yes. . .

228
00:18:19,971 --> 00:18:21,529
. . .but will l?

229
00:18:22,172 --> 00:18:23,809
Of course you will.

230
00:18:28,731 --> 00:18:32,406
l really have to go.
l have to go.

231
00:18:32,612 --> 00:18:34,329
You don't, you know.

232
00:18:35,971 --> 00:18:38,486
Yes, l do.

233
00:18:43,612 --> 00:18:45,364
l must see you again.

234
00:18:47,132 --> 00:18:49,599
-That's impossible.
-Why?

235
00:18:51,051 --> 00:18:52,723
Because. . .

236
00:18:55,211 --> 00:18:57,362
. . .l' m married.

237
00:19:59,612 --> 00:20:01,010
Good morning, Lisa.

238
00:20:01,211 --> 00:20:03,248
Good morning, doctor.
Your mail.

239
00:20:03,451 --> 00:20:06,250
Good. Please ask Janelle
to bring me my coffee.

240
00:20:06,451 --> 00:20:08,009
-Sure.
-Thank you.

241
00:20:08,571 --> 00:20:11,404
-Good morning, Sarah.
-Good morning, doctor.

242
00:20:11,612 --> 00:20:14,523
'''Twas the night before Christmas,
when all through the house...

243
00:20:14,731 --> 00:20:17,484
...not a creature was stirring,
not even a mouse. ''

244
00:20:21,491 --> 00:20:23,960
Okay. That's fine.
You can put your gown on.

245
00:20:28,491 --> 00:20:30,130
Hold this for Mommy.

246
00:20:31,652 --> 00:20:33,369
Looking forward to Christmas?

247
00:20:34,412 --> 00:20:36,049
Does this hurt?

248
00:20:49,771 --> 00:20:51,000
Right there?

249
00:21:01,531 --> 00:21:03,363
Daddy's gonna like that.

250
00:21:04,051 --> 00:21:05,690
Very good choice.

251
00:21:06,451 --> 00:21:08,682
''--before me. . .

252
00:21:09,172 --> 00:21:13,926
. . .when l jump into my bed. ''

253
00:21:15,852 --> 00:21:19,845
We should call the Zieglers
and thank them for the party.

254
00:21:20,771 --> 00:21:22,523
l've taken care of that.

255
00:21:24,092 --> 00:21:25,411
Good.

256
00:21:26,211 --> 00:21:29,567
So how do you feel about wrapping
the rest of the presents?

257
00:21:31,172 --> 00:21:33,288
